views.text: When you entrust your data to Microsoft 365, you remain the owner of that data.

We collect required diagnostic data to keep Microsoft 365 secure, up-to-date and performing as expected on the devices it’s installed on. This relates to the basic functioning of Microsoft 365 and doesn’t include your name, file content, or information about apps unrelated to Microsoft 365.
We’ve updated the privacy settings for Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Microsoft 365, OneNote and Loop to let you know what data we collect and how we use it. Let’s take a look.

We’d like you to share optional diagnostic and usage data about Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Microsoft 365, OneNote and Loop. It’s how we continue to improve. None of this data includes your name, file contents, or information about apps unrelated to Microsoft 365.

views.text: Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Microsoft 365, OneNote and Loop includes experiences that connect to online services—for example, downloadable templates from Office.com, and OneDrive file storage for sharing files with people you choose. When you use these experiences, Microsoft 365 collects diagnostic service data. In addition, some of these services analyze your content to deliver suggestions and recommendations.
